title: Saskatoon morning news rewind: Monday, Feb. 27
description: Here's a look back on who was on 'Global News Morning Saskatoon' for Monday, Feb. 27.

title: Developer confirms ‘secondary damage’ to Welland condo construction site following initial collapse
description: For the second time in February, the developer of a luxury condominium in Niagara Region reported structural damage in a south tower of the five storey project.

title: Twitter reportedly cuts 10% of workforce in latest round of cuts since Musk takeover
description: Twitter has laid off at least 200 employees, or about 10 per cent of its current workforce, the New York Times reported late on Sunday.

title: Feds’ 2023 budget should hike international aid group funding, agencies tell Freeland
description: As of late 2021, Prime Minister Justin Trudeau was still urging government ministers to increase Canada's international development assistance every year.

title: 2023 SAG Awards winners: Brendan Fraser, Ke Huy Quan earn more hardware
description: The SAG Awards, often an Oscar preview, threw some curve balls into the Oscars race.

title: Click named Blue Jays VP of baseball strategy
description: James Click was named the vice-president of baseball strategy for the Toronto Blue Jays on Monday.

title: Lethbridge police investigate assault at International Peace Pow-wow
description: Lethbridge police are investigating after an alleged assault took place at the Enmax Centre on the final day of the International Peace Pow-wow.

title: Prince Edward County OPP stop two ‘grandparent scammers’
description: An alleged 'grandparent scam' has been put to a stop by Prince Edward County OPP.

title: Man critically injured in Toronto police-involved shooting
description: Toronto police say an officer shot and critically injured a man shortly after it was reported a person had a knife in a park and was allegedly threatening people.

title: ANALYSIS: Slumping Jets need to find a solution
description: The Winnipeg Jets suddenly look like a gang that can't shoot straight. They need to find the solution — not any new teammates.
